                <h3>The Following is a timeline of Gandolfini's life:</h3>
                <ul style="list-style-position:outside; text-align:left; margin:30px;  color:black;">
                    <li><strong>1961</strong> - James Gandolfini is born in Westwood, NJ</li>
                    <li><strong>1979</strong> - Graduated Park Ridge Highschool</li>
                    <li><strong>1982</strong> - Graduated Rutgers University with a Bachelor of Arts in Communication Studies</li>
                    <li><strong>1992</strong> - Performs in Broadway show <i>On the Waterfront</i></li>
                    <li><strong>1999</strong> - The Sopranos debuts on HBO with Gandolfini the lead actor as Tony Soprano</li>
                    <li><strong>1999</strong> - Gets first emmy nomination for Outstanding Lead Actor (loses)</li>
                    <li><strong>2000</strong> - His son, Micheal Soprano is born</li>
                    <li><strong>2001</strong> - Wins first emmy for Outstanding Lead Actor</li>
                    <li><strong>2002</strong> - Divorces first wife, Macry Wudarski</li>
                    <li><strong>2007</strong> - Series finale of The Sopranos airs, with polorizing final scene</li>
                    <li><strong>2007</strong> - Visits and interviews injured Iraq War veterans for HBO documentary</li>
                    <li><strong>2008</strong> - Marries formaer model and actress Deborah Lin</li>
                    <li><strong>2009</strong> - Plays Mayor of New York in remake of <i>The Taking of Pelham 123</i></li>
                    <li><strong>2012</strong> - His daughter, Liliana Ruth Gandolfini, is born</li>
                    <li><strong>2013</strong> - James Gandolfini dies of a heart attack in Rome on a famly vacation</li>
                </ul>
